Title : To-Do List CLI Application

Introduction:

A To-Do List application helps users manage their daily tasks. Using Python lists and dictionaries, this project provides a simple command-line interface (CLI) to add, view, update, and delete tasks efficiently.

Problem Statement

People often struggle to remember their pending tasks. A simple task manager is needed that can store, update, and display tasks in an easy-to-use format.

Objectives:

Build a simple command-line app using Python lists & dictionaries.

Allow users to add, view, mark as done, and delete tasks.

Maintain tasks with unique IDs for better organization.

Provide an interactive menu-driven interface.

Methodology

Data Structure:

Tasks stored as a list of dictionaries ([{"id": 1, "task": "Example", "done": False}, ...]).

Operations Implemented:

Add Task → Append dictionary to list.

View Tasks → Display all tasks with their status.

Mark Done → Update dictionary value (done=True).

Delete Task → Remove dictionary from list by ID.

Flowchart:
          ┌──────────────────┐
          │  Start Program   │
          └───────┬──────────┘
                  │
        ┌─────────▼─────────┐
        │  Show Main Menu   │
        └───────┬──────────┘
                │
     ┌──────────▼───────────┐
     │  User Choice?         │
     └─┬─────────┬──────────┘
       │         │
   ┌───▼───┐ ┌───▼─────┐
   │ Add   │ │ View     │
   │ Task  │ │ Tasks    │
   └───┬───┘ └────┬─────┘
       │          │
   ┌───▼───┐  ┌───▼─────┐
   │ Mark  │  │ Delete  │
   │ Done  │  │ Task    │
   └───┬───┘  └────┬─────┘
       │          │
       └─────┬────┘
             ▼
     ┌──────────────┐
     │   Exit App   │
     └──────────────┘
